 <br>
<br>
   &quot;Dear Olendra and Donal,<br>
You know I am true.  I have travelled with your dear daughter for many years, more than I can remeber.  I remeber when I was but a young shaman just learning the ways of the spirits.<br>
  In my brash youth I decided you needed to get to know me and to put aside your wariness of me aside.  To do so I decided to come to your home and make you see who I truely was.  Here I was a BARBARIAN, and a shaman who still did not see the world as a place of danger but just as many wonders to see.  I can barging in and told you to stop being stupid.  If I remeber correctly you where astounded that I would take you on in your own city, and your own home.  <br>
   But, in me doing so I made you stop and think.  Adventually you came to love me as another if younger daughter.  I have loved you as another set of parents.  You have made me feel at home and safe when I felt lost in your world.  You helped me see some of the wonders that non elves never can slow down enough to see.  If it wasn't for you I would have never gotten to where I am now in my powers.<br>
    Now, as your adopted daughter, that young BRASH BARBARIAN, and as someone who loves you as much as Rhapsodey does, I'm going to tell you something you used to tell me over and over.   STOP AND THINK WITH YOUR HEADS NOT YOUR EMOTIONS!!!!!!!!!<br>
   Do you REALLY want assasins to KILL your only daughter?  Do you really wnat to ruin the happiness she has found???   If so then you are not the GOOD and HONOURABLE people you lead me to believe that you are.  If so then everything you taught me is a LIE.<br>
 <br>
    I can tell you true.  Rhapsodey is not the child whom ran off to see the world with me.  She has grown up and is making her own decisions.  You need to let her grown on her own.  She has grown into her own power as well.  In so doing she has seen most of the YOUNG court men to be shallow.  She found some one who loves her for herself and not for the power that being her consort or spouce would bring because she is YOUR DAUGHTER.  If you can not accept this then you have lost her and all of her love.  I cannot believe that you would be willing to do that.  <br>
 <br>
   Olendra,  as a woman you KNOW that she NEEDS to feel love and to have some one to cherish.  Even if she can only cherish him for a little while and him her that love will last forever.  Who is to say that when he must pass from this life that because of his love for her that she will not be STRONGER for it.<br>
 <br>
   I love you truely.  Please let them be.  I have met this Phreezin.  He is brave, stronge, caring, and has the heart of a noble.  As to his liniage,  You know we have no &quot;nobles&quot; in our lands.  But, I can tell you he has passed the MOST rigorous trials we have to chose our cheifs.  If he where not still hunting the great lands beyond our frozen peaks he would be considered one of our greatest cheifs.  He has also helped save many lands from evil forces.<br>
   If this is not enough to make him more &quot;appropriate&quot; then think on this,  I have spoken with the sprits of my land and they have fortold many  things that he will accomplish.  You know my oath to the spirits to not state a lie,  so please consider carefully what you want to do.<br>
 <br>
<br>
       Love, Respect,  and may the Sprits Guide You,<br>
 <br>
        Your Loving Barbarian Shaman<br>
         Reoki <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bsphereofhonour58352.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sornwolf>Sorn Wolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#330000>(12/27/01 11:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Reoki's letter</span><hr size=1> Meanwhile in The Freeport Region In a quiet Tavern.  Rhapsodey is enjoying a Quiet meal after her message to her Father.<br>
<br>
She hears a Familiar voice from behind her.  Rhapsodey ive come to take you home.  She turns.  Kulwein no dont tell me you to have come at my fathers wim to get me.  I wont go Kulwein and I dont want to fight you.  So please dont try because I will kill you if I need to.<br>
<br>
Kuwlein you know me.  You were even in the lands of overtheir that day.  Dont tell me that my fathers words and offer of money has closed your eyes to the truth.  You have hunted with me long enough to know that no one can make me do anything against my will.<br>
<br>
So what will it be Kulwein.  Are you going to try to take me home or are you going to walk away like I was never here.  If you must follow my fathers orders I promise I will not go willingly and you will not return me alive <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bsphereofhonour58352.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sornwolf>Sorn Wolf</A> at: 12/27/01 11:51:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bsphereofhonour58352.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nellen1>Nellen1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#330000>(12/27/01 12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Leave her be</span><hr size=1> Kulwein,<br>
<br>
