<br>
Shortly she has arrived outside of the Bandit camp.  The whimpers of pain from the Captive tears at her heart as she carefully surveys the camp and the surroundings to be shore that their is to be no surprises awaiting her.  Finally the cry of her ancient weapons desire for vengeance for the crimes committed to the young bards and the cry of Mercy from their <br>
prisoner overcome her wariness.  With a Scream of rage Rhapsodey appears among the bandits her ancient mace Flameweaver delivering fiery death in one hand and the Sword Frostbringer delivering icy death in the other.  Her every attack is aimed to deliver instant death.<br>
<br>
Quickly the battle is over.  She quickly check her surroundings and the bodies to make sure their are no survivors.  Tears coming to her eyes as she softly sings a song of passing <br>
for those that have been killed by the bandits and for the Bandits themselves to ease their passage to the afterlife.<br>
<br>
She turns to the Bandits prisoner and finds him staring wide eyed at her from the tree they had him tied to.  Sheathing her weapons she quickly cuts the prisoner free.  As she gently<br>
lowers him to the ground.  <br>
<br>
Rhapsodey.&quot; you are safe.  Stay still now im going to check you injuries.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rhapsodey quickly checks the young wizards injuries as she sings a song of healing and comfort.  Her attention is so focused on her work that she does not notice the actions of<br>
the young wizzard as he draws a Dagger from his robes.  With Practiced ease he locates a weak Point in her Dark Blue armor and rams the dagger home into her side.<br>
<br>
Rhapsodey Screams in pain at the sudden pain in her side.  Her years of training quickly take over as she tumbles away from the threat.  Coming quickly to her feet she draws <br>
her Sword Frostbringer as she turns her now useless right arm away from her enemy.<br>
<br>
Young Wizard,&quot;Sorry Rhapsodey the reward for you was just to much to resist.  Nothing Personal I hope you understand.  Your Fathers Agents provided me with the poison that <br>
coats the blade that I used on you.  I would advise against killing me because the poison is lethal over time without the antidote and I don't have the antidote with me so their is<br>
no use killing me and taking it from my body.  Now why don't you be a good girl and put your weapons away before the poison paralyzes you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rhapsodey Screams with Rage and with every ounce of her strength Throws her Sword at the young Wizard.  Her aim proves true and she strikes her Target through the heart.  Flames of rage still burning in her eyes she walks to the body and pulls her sword from the now Frozen corpse.  As she does Frostbringer turns his every effort to saving his Wielder as he quickly chills her body to slow the spread of the lethal poison.<br>
<br>
Frostbringer having now chilled her nearly to freezing begins to prompt her now cold stricken mind to head to the safety of the Barbarian fishing village and to the Safety Of her Sword Sister Reoki who is their seeing to the injured from a recent Rabid bear Attack.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bsphereofhonour58352.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kulwein>Kulwein</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brother of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#330000>(12/31/01 6:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Villian Wanted Dead.  And Daughter Returned Safely</span><hr size=1> WHAT DID I SAY ABOUT ATTACKING RHAPSODEY! Thats is...time to gother my alliances and pull long favors long owed, if you cant accept the love of your daughter by the time my forces are set i will have no choice! I seek the leadership to aid me at my side, my best trusted friend Phreezin. If you get this in time, i seek your aide to lead an attack! A time for talking did not work, they seeked action now we must do the same. The prize loot we are seeking is an antidote, and this is a no drop item off of Rhapsodey's father. Its her of him....and im sad to say that we choose you sir! You have till our troups get organized! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/ureokikvatra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>REOKI   KVATRA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Defender of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#330000>(12/31/01 10:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   