      Unbeknown to me my dearest friend was in the greatest need of me in her life.<br>
      As I finished up with Trenton my faithful hounds came barging into the local midwife/healers house where I was working.  Trying to push them back out the door I suddenly know they need me somewhere with all haste.  I rush out the door and into the village I grab all of my medicine bags.  Yelling, “Men I need a few of you to come with me now.”  Trenton’s two brothers, Jakath and Klartoth, join in my mad rush to follow my hounds.<br>
      My hounds lead me out into the Plains of Western Karana.  Finally, in the distance I see a form laying prone on the ground.  As I approach I notice that is holding a sword and that it is slowly moving in my direction as if being dragged.  The closer I get the more worried I get, for the form is in Blue armor.  When I get to the body it stops moving.  <br>
      I stop by the body and start crying.<br>
      The body at my feet is Rhapsodey, my sword sister.   She is frozen solid.  I bend over and pick up her frostweaver.  She has told me it was alive and I have seen stranger things.<br>
      Quietly, in the deepest part of my soul I hear a voice that I have never heard before.  “Thank you for coming.  My bondmate needs your help.  I know I can trust you.  I have frozen her because she has been poisoned.  She would not have made it to you if she were not frozen.  But hurry time is against her,” it whispers.<br>
       Standing up straight so fast I startle the two men. “All right, Donal if this is how you wish it I will have no sympathy for you.   You and your SHALL suffer,” I scream.<br>
      Digging through my medicine bags I start to get everything I need to deal with poisons.  “Jakath, I need you to start a fire.  Klartoth, go get some water from the stream and get it boiling over the fire,” I tell them.<br>
     I wrap Rhapsodey in all the blankets and spare cloth in my packs.  I then start to pray, “Oh Great Spirits hear my plead.  I plead with you to take the poison out of my swordsister’s blood and purify her.  Save her life and do not let it leave this body yet.  She has done no wrong here, her father who does not want to see the truth has injured her in more ways than just this poison that he has let evil persons put in her blood.”<br>
     As I pray my hands start to glow.  Steam begins to form off of Rhapsodey's body as she warms.   Soon, thick black ooze starts to appear out of her mouth.  This I wipe away.  All of a sudden she starts to cough.  <br>
     “She is breathing.  Thank You Great Spirit,” I pray.<br>
      I have the men start to make a camp for us.  While they do that I check Rhapsodey over to make sure there are no other wounds to be dealt with.  Thankfully there are no other wounds, but I am still worried.  She should be waking up now.  I then pick up the sword again.<br>
       “What is still wrong?” I ask.  <br>
       “Her soul was hurt more deeply than even I feared by her father’s treachery.  She will not awake till she is called by her true love.” It replied.  “And, because her heart is still tied to music she must be called by song.”<br>
         With this advice in mind I call one of my hounds.  Scribbling a message to Phreezin, I then stuff it into her collar.<br>
         “Go.  Go find Phreezin.  Hurry my dear.”  I tell her.<br>
          She starts to run away into the plains.  She starts to go faster and faster.  Soon she is going faster than any mortal mutt can go.  I know she will find Phreezin in time.<br>
           Time passes, and Rhapsodey does not stir.  Finally Phreezin appears.<br>
           I tell him what has happened as quickly as I can.  I also tell him what he must do.<br>
           “Me, I am to sing her back?  Why can’t you do something?  I do not know how to sing.”  He says with tear filled eyes.<br>
            “It has been given to you to do.  Sing her what comes from your heart.  Do not care for the words or tune, just that what you sing to her be true.”<br>
          <br>
<br>
 <p>Love and Respect Always<BR>Reoki Kvatra<BR>Shaman of the 40th Moon</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bsphereofhonour58352.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nellen1>Nellen1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#330000>(1/1/02 3:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   In words and song, be healed</span><hr size=1> Me? I cannot sing. I dont know how. I'm no good!<br>
